ce:section.ce:para:
Conversion of the intermittent solar energy to the storable hydrogen energy by photoelectrochemical (PEC) water splitting has been one of the most prospective technologies for a sustainable society [1,2]. Among multifarious materials for PEC water splitting, the monoclinic scheelite bismuth vanadate (BiVO4) has been a research hotspot owing to its stable in aqueous media and proper bandgap of 2.4 eV for visible light photocatalysis [1–3]. However, PEC water splitting performance of BiVO4 is limited by the efficiencies of charge separation (

                           η

